## 2026-04-04 - styleSync.ts silently swallows parse failures for color tokens and gradient stops
- Fixed `applyPaintStyle` to throw with a descriptive error when `parseColor` returns null, instead of silently skipping the paint update. Moved parse call before style creation to avoid leaving empty Figma styles behind on failure.
- Fixed `applyGradientPaintStyle` to parse all stops upfront, collect failures with their indices and unparseable values, and throw a descriptive error listing each failed stop (e.g., "2 of 5 gradient stops could not be parsed: stop 1 ("#gggggg"), stop 3 (null)"). Also added an upfront check for stops.length < 2. Style is no longer created when stops are invalid.
- Errors surface through the existing `failures` array in `styles-applied`, which the UI already displays to users as "Push: N/M applied (failed: …)".

